@node Usage
@next Usage
@prev Usage
First of all @{b}@{u}make a backup@{ub}@{uu} of the partition !!!

Stop all background programs or even better start without startup-sequence
before optimizing a partition.

After starting the DiskOptimizer select the partition and the options.

Workbench Mode: If enabled Icons will be loaded faster but directory-listings
                will be a bit slower.

Fast Files: A selectable number of the first blocks of the files will be
            placed directly after the directory and therefore reading the
            first block(s) of the file (file-type analysing) will be faster.

O. for Read Only: Optimize for Reading, use this if you don't write (much)
                  to this disk for example your 'Workbench'-Partition.
                  If you disable this feature writing to the disk will be
                  faster

By selecting 'Start' the partition will be read and some infos about
the partition will be displayed.
When the data is read optimizing will start after a warning requester.
If you select 'yes' in the requester the partition will be optimized.
WARNING: After this requester you CAN'T STOP optimizing !!!
@endnode

@node History
@next History
@prev History
1.1 - Using the stop-gadget did not stop optimizing and when selecting 'Yes'
      in the requester this could destroy the data on the partition.
      Bug removed.
1.3 - Fixed some bugs in the GUI
1.4 - DiskOptimizer did crash when trying to optimize an empty partition.
1.7 - Support for 64 bit NSD/TD64 enabled.
@endnode
